              <img src="/images/slides/facebook.jpg" alt="">
              <span id="facebook">Facebook</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <img src="/images/slides/gmail.jpg" alt="">
              <span id="gmail" >Gmail</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p id="serviceTagline">
          <span>Click the turtle in your</span><span id="service">&nbsp;</span><span>to <a class="b-blue" href="#mitm_proof">"MITM-proof"</a> your message.</span>
        </p>

        <p id="serviceTaglineMobile">
          Click the turtle to <a class="b-blue" href="#mitm_proof">"MITM-proof"</a> your message.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>
    <!-- carousel -->

    <div class="container">
      <p class="first">
        MITM-proof communication through almost any website, with zero intervention needed from the site operators.
      </p>

      <p>
        okTurtles is designed with the potential to work over almost any website. All it needs to create an encrypted message for someone is the identity of that person, specifically, their public key. Unlike the system that HTTPS uses today, okTurtles is able to securely obtain this information by using DNSChain.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- <section id="unblock"> -->
